[7]Pinus ayacahuite is native to the mountains of southern Mexico and Western central America, in the Sierra Madre del Sur and the eastern end of the axis volcanic transversal, between 14째 and 21째 of north latitude in the mexican States of Guerrero, Oaxaca, Puebla, Veracruz and Chiapas, and in Guatemala, Salvador and Honduras.
[8]The tree believes in areas that are relatively humid with summer rains, however, specimens from the east and south of its distribution, living conditions are particularly damp ; it requires good sunlight and well-drained soil.
[9]On average, over the year, the temperature fluctuates from 19 째 to 10 째 C.
